hpicfIpRouting.name: hpicfIpRouting

revisions.description: Added hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdTable to provide BFD support to Static Routes.
Added hpicfIpv6RouterAdvertRtrPreference, hpicfIpv6RtrAdvParamGroup and hpicfIpv6RtrAdvParamCompliance. Deprecated hpicfIpv6RtrAdvGroup and hpicfIpv6RtrAdvCompliance.
Changed syntax and description of hpicfIpStaticRouteLogging
Added ICMP Rate Limiting and Directed Broadcast forwarding objects.

hpicfIpRouting.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfIpRouting.description: This MIB module contains HP proprietary objects for managing IP Routing.

hpicfRdiscAdminStatus.name: hpicfRdiscAdminStatus
hpicfRdiscAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the ICMP Router Discovery protocol.

hpicfRdiscIfCfgTable.name: hpicfRdiscIfCfgTable
hpicfRdiscIfCfgTable.description: Per-interface configuration for the ICMP Router Discovery protocol.

hpicfRdiscIfCfgEntry.name: hpicfRdiscIfCfgEntry
hpicfRdiscIfCfgEntry.description: Router discovery configuration information for a single interface.

hpicfRdiscIfAdminStatus.name: hpicfRdiscIfAdminStatus
hpicfRdiscIfAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the ICMP Router Discovery protocol on this interface.

hpicfRdiscIfAdvertAddress.name: hpicfRdiscIfAdvertAddress
hpicfRdiscIfAdvertAddress.description: The destination address to be used for router advertisements on this interface. If the value of this object is 'multicast' (the default), router advertisements sent on this interface will be sent to the all-hosts multicast address, 224.0.0.1. If the value of this object is 'broadcast', router advertisements sent on this interface will be sent to the limited broadcast address, 255.255.255.255.

hpicfRdiscIfMaxAdvertInterval.name: hpicfRdiscIfMaxAdvertInterval
hpicfRdiscIfMaxAdvertInterval.description: The maximum time allowed between sending unsolicited Router Advertisements on this interface.

hpicfRdiscIfMinAdvertInterval.name: hpicfRdiscIfMinAdvertInterval
hpicfRdiscIfMinAdvertInterval.description: The minimum time allowed between sending unsolicited Router Advertisements on this interface. Must be no greater than hpicfRdiscMaxAdvertInterval.

hpicfRdiscIfAdvertLifetime.name: hpicfRdiscIfAdvertLifetime
hpicfRdiscIfAdvertLifetime.description: The value to be placed in the Lifetime field of Router Advertisements sent on this interface. Must be no less than hpicfRdiscMaxAdvertInterval.

hpicfRdiscIfPreference.name: hpicfRdiscIfPreference
hpicfRdiscIfPreference.description: The preference of the router as a default router, relative to the other routers on the same subnet. Higher values are more preferable. The minimum value (0x80000000) is used to indicate that the router, even though it may be advertised, is not to be used by neighboring hosts as a default router.

hpicfIcmpReplyLimit.name: hpicfIcmpReplyLimit
hpicfIcmpReplyLimit.description: The maximum number of icmp replies to send per second.

hpicfIcmpEchoBroadcastReplyEnable.name: hpicfIcmpEchoBroadcastReplyEnable
hpicfIcmpEchoBroadcastReplyEnable.description: Enable/Disable echo replies to directed broadcast echo requests..

hpicfIpMaximumPaths.name: hpicfIpMaximumPaths
hpicfIpMaximumPaths.description: Maximum number of equal cost paths to a destination that we will add to the IP routing table.

hpicfDBroadcastFwdAcl.name: hpicfDBroadcastFwdAcl
hpicfDBroadcastFwdAcl.description: This object contains the ACL to apply to IP Directed Broadcast packets.The value is the name of an existing IP ACL defined using the Command Line Interface (CLI) or a zero length string if there is no ACL applied. This object can only be set when hpicfDBroadcastFwdEnable is also set to 'enable' in the same request. Setting hpicfBroadcastFwdEnable to 'enable' without also setting this object will clear this object and unapply any IP Directed Broadcast ACL.

hpicfIpStaticRouteTable.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteTable
hpicfIpStaticRouteTable.description: Table of configured IP static routes. This table uses a protocol-independent format, so that it can be used for both IPv4 and IPv6 static routes. Rows configured in this table should be stored in non-volatile storage.

hpicfIpStaticRouteEntry.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteEntry
hpicfIpStaticRouteEntry.description: A row in the static route table, containing information about a single configured static route. There are 3 legal cases for the indexing this table: 1. ((hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddrType == hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixType) && (hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddr is IP address of appropriate type) && (hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdIfIndex == 0)) Normal, remote static route. hpicfIpStaticRouteType will be equal to 'remote'. Note that the first condition that the FwdAddrType must equal the PrefixType exactly is not strictly true. For example, in IPv6, it is quite legal and expected to configure a static route where the PrefixType is ipv6, and the Prefix is a 16 byte IPv6 destination address, but the FwdAddrType is ipv6z and the FwdAddr is a 20 byte scoped IPv6 link-local address. 2. ((hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddrType == 'unknown') && (hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddr == zero-length string) && (hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdIfIndex != 0)) Interface route. Treated like a connected route. hpicfIpStaticRouteType will be equal to 'local'. 3. ((hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddrType == 'unknown') && (hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddr == zero-length string) && (hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdIfIndex == 0)) Discard route. hpicfStaticRouteType will be equal to either 'reject' or 'discard'.

hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixType.name: hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixType
hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixType.description: The type of destination prefix specified by this route. The value 'dns(16)' is not supported. This object specifies the type of destination address prefix in the hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefix object.

hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefix.name: hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefix
hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefix.description: The destination address prefix of this route. The type of address specified by this route is indicated by the corresponding instance of the hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixType object. An attempt to create a row in which the length of this object is not consistent with the type specified by hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixType must be rejected. An attempt to create a row in which the value X of this object, logically ANDed with the value of the mask formed from the corresponding instance of the hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixLength object, is not equal to X must be rejected, i.e., this prefix may not have any 'host' bits set.

hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixLength.name: hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixLength
hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixLength.description: This object indicates the number of leading one bits which form the mask to be logically ANDed with a destination address before comparison with the corresponding instance of the hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefix object for a route match operation. An attempt to create a row in which the value of this object is longer than the maximum legal length of an address of the type indicated by the corresponding instance of the hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixType object must be rejected. An attempt to create a row in which the value of the mask formed from this object logically ANDed with the value of the corresponding instance of the hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefix object is not equal to the hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefix.

hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddrType.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddrType
hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddrType.description: The type of forwarding address for this route. The value of this object must be equal either to 'unknown' or to a value appropriate for the corresponding instance of the hpicfIpStaticRoutePrefixType object. For non-remote routes, the value of this object must be 'unknown'.

hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddr.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddr
hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddr.description: For remote routes, the value of the next specified router to use for forwarding packets to the destination specified by this route. Note that this router does not need to be directly connected. In the case where it is not, the actual routing table entry will use a next hop determined by looking up the best route to this forwarding address. For non-remote routes, the value of this object will be a zero-length string. An attempt to create a row in which the length of this object is not consistent with the type specified by hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdAddrType must be rejected. An attempt to create a row with a value for this object other than a zero-length string must be rejected if the corresponding instance of the hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdIfIndex object is non-zero.

hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdIfIndex.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdIfIndex
hpicfIpStaticRouteFwdIfIndex.description: For remote routes, the value of this object must be zero. For reject or blackhole routes, the value of this object must be zero. For local routes, this object indicates the ifIndex of the local interface to use to reach this destination.

hpicfIpStaticRouteType.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteType
hpicfIpStaticRouteType.description: The type of route. The value 'other' is not supported, and is included only for compatibility with the IP Forwarding Table MIB. The value 'local' indicates that the destination is treated as if it were directly connected. The value 'remote' indicates that the forwarding address will be used to reach the destination. The value 'reject' indicates that if this route is matched, a packet to the destination is discarded and a notification (e.g. ICMP error) is returned to the packet sender. The value 'blackhole' indicates that if the route is matched, a packet to the destination is silently dropped. The value of this object must be consistent with the forwarding address information used to index the route.

hpicfIpStaticRouteDistance.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteDistance
hpicfIpStaticRouteDistance.description: The administrative distance to associate with this static route. Routes with lower distances are preferred. By default, static routes are created with an administrative distance of 1, meaning they are preferred over all routes except directly connected routes. Setting a higher administrative distance for a route can be used for the following reasons: - by configuring multiple static routes to the same destination, one with the default distance and one with a higher distance, one can configure backup static routes - by configuring a static route with an administrative distance higher than the distance for a particular dynamic routing protocol, one can allow a static route to be overridden by dynamic routing information. Routes with an administrative distance of 255 will never be entered in the routing table.

hpicfIpStaticRouteTag.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteTag
hpicfIpStaticRouteTag.description: Tag value that can be used to filter redistribution of this route via route maps.

hpicfIpStaticRouteStatus.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteStatus
hpicfIpStaticRouteStatus.description: Status of this route entry. All writable columns in this table can be modified while the corresponding row is active.

hpicfIpStaticRouteMetric.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteMetric
hpicfIpStaticRouteMetric.description: Metric value for this route. It is used to compare static route with other static routes to the same destination. The acceptable range is from 1 to 255, both inclusive.

hpicfIpStaticRouteName.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteName
hpicfIpStaticRouteName.description: Name of the configured static route. It is used for lucidity and troubleshooting purpose and is optional.

hpicfIpStaticRouteLogging.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteLogging
hpicfIpStaticRouteLogging.description: This object determines whether or not debug log messages are to be generated for packets matching statically configured blackhole routes. When enabled, the debug option 'ip/ipv6 fib blackhole' needs to be enabled in order to print the log messages to a specified destination.

hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdEnable.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdEnable
hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdEnable.description: This object enables or disables BFD on Static route. When set to true(1), BFD is enabled for the session. When set to false(2), BFD is disabled for the session.

hpicfIpStaticNeighborTable.name: hpicfIpStaticNeighborTable
hpicfIpStaticNeighborTable.description: Table of configured IP static neighbors. This table uses a protocol-independent format, so that it can be used for both IPv4 and IPv6 static neighbors. Rows configured in this table should be stored in non-volatile storage.

hpicfIpStaticNeighborEntry.name: hpicfIpStaticNeighborEntry
hpicfIpStaticNeighborEntry.description: A row in the static neighbor table, containing information about a single configured static neighbor.

hpicfIpStaticNeighborIfIndex.name: hpicfIpStaticNeighborIfIndex
hpicfIpStaticNeighborIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value for the interface used to reach this neighbor.

hpicfIpStaticNeighborNetAddrType.name: hpicfIpStaticNeighborNetAddrType
hpicfIpStaticNeighborNetAddrType.description: The type of network address specified by this entry. Only the values 'ipv4(1)' and 'ipv6(2)' are expected. This object specifies the type of neighbor network address prefix in the hpicfIpStaticNeighborNetAddress object.

hpicfIpStaticNeighborNetAddress.name: hpicfIpStaticNeighborNetAddress
hpicfIpStaticNeighborNetAddress.description: The neighbor network address of this configured static neighbor. The type of address specified by this entry is indicated by the corresponding instance of the hpicfIpStaticNeighborNetAddrType object. An attempt to create a row in which the length of this object is not consistent with the type specified by hpicfIpStaticNeighborNetAddrType must be rejected.

hpicfIpStaticNeighborPhysAddress.name: hpicfIpStaticNeighborPhysAddress
hpicfIpStaticNeighborPhysAddress.description: The media-dependent physical address used to reach this neighbor. The size of this address depends on the media type of the interface identified by hpicfIpStaticNeighborIfIndex.

hpicfIpStaticNeighborStatus.name: hpicfIpStaticNeighborStatus
hpicfIpStaticNeighborStatus.description: Status of this neighbor entry. All writable columns in this table can be modified while the corresponding row is active.

hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdTable.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdTable
hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdTable.description: Extension of Static Route table to enable BFD on Static routes.

hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdEntry.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdEntry
hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdEntry.description: Static route BFD table contains BFD objects. This table is added to provide BFD support to Static Routes. This is the additional param of Static Route table. The Value of Index in BFD table should be as same in Static Route table. 1. While enabling BFD static route, verify the RowStatus of hpicfIpStaticRouteTable for the configured index. 2. If Rowstatus is not present in hpicfIpStaticRouteTable Create Rowstatus for that recIndex in hpicfIpStaticRouteTable and then create the RowStatus in hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdTable. 3. While disabling the bfd Status, Destroy the rowstatus in hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdTable.

hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdSrcAddrType.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdSrcAddrType
hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdSrcAddrType.description: The type of IP address used as source address for BFD

hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdSrcAddr.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdSrcAddr
hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdSrcAddr.description: The IP address which is used as source address for BFD

hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdDstAddrType.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdDstAddrType
hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdDstAddrType.description: The type of IP address used as destination address for BFD

hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdDstAddr.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdDstAddr
hpicfIpStaticRouteBfdDstAddr.description: The IP address which is used as destination address for BFD

hpicfIpCidrRouteEntry.name: hpicfIpCidrRouteEntry
hpicfIpCidrRouteEntry.description: Extended information about a single route.

hpicfIpCidrRouteDistance.name: hpicfIpCidrRouteDistance
hpicfIpCidrRouteDistance.description: The administrative distance of this route.

hpicfInetCidrRouteEntry.name: hpicfInetCidrRouteEntry
hpicfInetCidrRouteEntry.description: Extended information about a single route.

hpicfInetCidrRouteDistance.name: hpicfInetCidrRouteDistance
hpicfInetCidrRouteDistance.description: The administrative distance of this route.

hpicfInetCidrRouteInfo.name: hpicfInetCidrRouteInfo
hpicfInetCidrRouteInfo.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this route, as determined by the value specified in the route's inetCidrRouteProto value. If this information is not present, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }, which is a syntactically valid object identifier, and any implementation conforming to ASN.1 and the Basic Encoding Rules must be able to generate and recognize this value.

hpicfInetCidrRouteStatsTable.name: hpicfInetCidrRouteStatsTable
hpicfInetCidrRouteStatsTable.description: HP extensions to the InetCidrRouteTable for scalar stats

hpicfInetCidrRouteStatsEntry.name: hpicfInetCidrRouteStatsEntry
hpicfInetCidrRouteStatsEntry.description: Extended information about a scalar stats of the route.

hpicfInetCidrNumRouteDestinations.name: hpicfInetCidrNumRouteDestinations
hpicfInetCidrNumRouteDestinations.description: Total number of destinations for a particular inetCidrRouteDestType.

hpicfInetCidrNumRouteRoutes.name: hpicfInetCidrNumRouteRoutes
hpicfInetCidrNumRouteRoutes.description: Total number of routes for a particular inetCidrRouteDestType.

hpicfArpAgingTime.name: hpicfArpAgingTime
hpicfArpAgingTime.description: The timeout period in minutes for aging out an arp entry in the arp cache. Default value is 20 minutes. Allowable values for the HP implementation are 1-1440 and 0. The value of 0 indicates that an infinite ageout is to be used. The value 16666666 minutes (32 years) is used internally to effectively indicate an infinite timeout.

hpicfArpMcastReplies.name: hpicfArpMcastReplies
hpicfArpMcastReplies.description: This object is used to enable/disable Multicast MAC support in all multicast modes. It will be disabled by default.

hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixTable.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixTable
hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixTable.description: Table of default routers learnt through auto-config This Table will be used in conjunction of ipDefaultRouterTable defined in RFC 4293 to get the attributes of the default routers learnt through auto-config

hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixEntry.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixEntry
hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixEntry.description: A row in the default router table, containing information about a single learnt default router

hpicfIpDefaultRouterAddressType.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterAddressType
hpicfIpDefaultRouterAddressType.description: The address type of the default router. The only supported type is IPV6 as of now

hpicfIpDefaultRouterAddress.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterAddress
hpicfIpDefaultRouterAddress.description: The address of the default router.

hpicfIpDefaultRouterIfIndex.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterIfIndex
hpicfIpDefaultRouterIfIndex.description: The address of the default router.

hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixOnLink.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixOnLink
hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixOnLink.description: The object has the value true (1) if the prefix can be used for on-link determination, otherwise the value is false(2)

hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixAutonomous.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixAutonomous
hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixAutonomous.description: The object has the value true(1) if this prefix can be used for autonomous address configuration. If the value is false(2), the prefix is not used to autoconfigure a local interface address

hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixValidLifeTime.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixValidLifeTime
hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixValidLifeTime.description: The valid life time for the router.

hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixPrefdLifeTime.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixPrefdLifeTime
hpicfIpDefaultRouterPrefixPrefdLifeTime.description: The preferred life time for the router.

hpicfIpDefaultRouterEntry.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterEntry
hpicfIpDefaultRouterEntry.description: Extended information about a single route.

hpicfIpDefaultRouterMTU.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterMTU
hpicfIpDefaultRouterMTU.description: The link MTU size advertised by the router. The selected Mlink TU may be different from this one.

hpicfIpDefaultRouterHopLimit.name: hpicfIpDefaultRouterHopLimit
hpicfIpDefaultRouterHopLimit.description: The hop limit to be used by the host on outgoing packets.

hpicfIpv6NDRAAdminStatus.name: hpicfIpv6NDRAAdminStatus
hpicfIpv6NDRAAdminStatus.description: A flag indicating whether or not the router sends periodic router advertisements and responds to router solicitations.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixTable.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixTable
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixTable.description: This table describes the router advertisement configuration variables for each interface.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixIfIndex.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixIfIndex
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface on which this prefix is configured. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of the IF-MIB's ifIndex.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixPrefix.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixPrefix
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixPrefix.description: The address prefix. The address type of this object is specified in hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixType. The length of this object is the standard length for objects of that type.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixLength.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixLength
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixLength.description: The prefix length associated with this prefix. The value 0 has no special meaning for this object. It simply refers to address '::/0'.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixOnLinkFlag.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixOnLinkFlag
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixOnLinkFlag.description: Router Advertisement messages are sent out with the On-Link flag (L-bit) field set to this value.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixAutonomousFlag.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixAutonomousFlag
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixAutonomousFlag.description: Autonomous address configuration flag. Router Advertisement messages are sent out with the autonomous flag field set to this value in the Prefix Information.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixLifetimeType.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixLifetimeType
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixLifetimeType.description: Specifies if the hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixPreferredLifetime and hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixValidLifetime are of the kind where consecutive advertisements have the same time(fixed) or a time that decrements in real time. The realTime(2) can be used to specify a time in future at which the LifeTimes become zero.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixPreferredLifetime.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixPreferredLifetime
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixPreferredLifetime.description: The length of time ,in seconds,that this prefix will be preferred. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity. The Router Advertisement messages are sent out with the Preferred LifeTime field set to this value. To specify in a realTime way,set this object to a future time in number of seconds since January 1, 1990, Coordinated Universal Time and also set hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixTimeType to realTime. The default value is 7 days(604800 seconds) fixed time

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixValidLifetime.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixValidLifetime
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixValidLifetime.description: The length of time, in seconds, that this prefix will continue to be valid, i.e. time until invalidation. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity. The Router advertisement messages are sent out with the Valid LifeTime field set to this value. To specify in a realTime way,set this object to a future time in number of seconds since January 1, 1990, Coordinated Universal Time and also set hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixTimeType to realTime. The default value is 30 days (or 2592000 seconds) fixed time.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixRowStatus.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixRowStatus
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. As all objects in this conceptual row have default values a row can be created and made active by setting this object appropriately.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixAdvertiseFlag.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixAdvertiseFlag
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixAdvertiseFlag.description: Specifies whether the prefix in this entry is advertised or not.When set to TRUE prefix is advertised.

HpicfIpRouteProtoName.name: HpicfIpRouteProtoName
HpicfIpRouteProtoName.description: An enumerated value which indicates the protocol name for show IP route summary.

hpicfIpRouteSummaryTable.name: hpicfIpRouteSummaryTable
hpicfIpRouteSummaryTable.description: IP route summary table in global context.

hpicfIpRouteProto.name: hpicfIpRouteProto
hpicfIpRouteProto.description: Protocol names that are enabled and active.

hpicfIpRouteCnt.name: hpicfIpRouteCnt
hpicfIpRouteCnt.description: count of active routes per routing protocol.

HpicfIpv6RouteProtoName.name: HpicfIpv6RouteProtoName
HpicfIpv6RouteProtoName.description: An enumerated value which indicates the protocol name for show IPv6 route summary.

hpicfIpv6RouteSummaryTable.name: hpicfIpv6RouteSummaryTable
hpicfIpv6RouteSummaryTable.description: IPv6 route summary table in the global context.

hpicfIpv6RouteProto.name: hpicfIpv6RouteProto
hpicfIpv6RouteProto.description: IPv6 route protocol names that are enabled and active.

hpicfIpv6RouteCnt.name: hpicfIpv6RouteCnt
hpicfIpv6RouteCnt.description: A count of active IPv6 routes per routing protocol.

hpicfIpRouteCount.name: hpicfIpRouteCount
hpicfIpRouteCount.description: This parameter specifies total number of routes in the Routing table.

hpicfIpRouteNextHopCount.name: hpicfIpRouteNextHopCount
hpicfIpRouteNextHopCount.description: This parameter specifies total number of next-hop entries in the Routing table. This parameter is useful to know how many other routers are connected and acting as a next-hop router for this router

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvTable.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvTable
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvTable.description: This table augments ipv6RouterAdvertEntry and it contains HP proprietary objects for managing router advertisements.

hpicfIpv6NDRADNSAdminStatus.name: hpicfIpv6NDRADNSAdminStatus
hpicfIpv6NDRADNSAdminStatus.description: A flag indicating whether or not the router includes DNS options with periodic router advertisements.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvEntry.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvEntry
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvEntry.description: An entry in the hpicfIpv6RtrAdvEntry contains Router Advertisement parameters.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvCurHopLimitMode.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvCurHopLimitMode
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvCurHopLimitMode.description: This object indicates whether the value in ipv6RouterAdvertCurHopLimit is in use or the value in ipv6IpDefaultHopLimit is in use for an entry in this table. A set to 'global' means: - ipv6IpDefaultHopLimit value will be used for hop limit. A set to 'perInterface' means: - ipv6RouterAdvertCurHopLimit value will be used for hop limit.

hpicfIpv6RouterAdvertSendDNSAdverts.name: hpicfIpv6RouterAdvertSendDNSAdverts
hpicfIpv6RouterAdvertSendDNSAdverts.description: A flag indicating whether or not the router includes DNS options in periodic router advertisements on this interface.

hpicfIpv6RouterAdvertRtrPreference.name: hpicfIpv6RouterAdvertRtrPreference
hpicfIpv6RouterAdvertRtrPreference.description: Indicates whether to prefer this router over other default routers.

hpicfRdiscBaseGroup.name: hpicfRdiscBaseGroup
hpicfRdiscBaseGroup.description: Basic ICMP Router Discovery configuration objects.

hpicfRdiscIfCfgGroup.name: hpicfRdiscIfCfgGroup
hpicfRdiscIfCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects allowing per-interface configuration of ICMP Router Discovery operation.

hpicfIcmpReplyBaseGroup.name: hpicfIcmpReplyBaseGroup
hpicfIcmpReplyBaseGroup.description: A collection of objects allowing configuration of ICMP Redirect operation.

hpicfIcmpReplyLimitGroup.name: hpicfIcmpReplyLimitGroup
hpicfIcmpReplyLimitGroup.description: A collection of objects allowing configuration of ICMP Reply rate limiting.

hpicfIpRouteCfgGroup.name: hpicfIpRouteCfgGroup
hpicfIpRouteCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects allowing configuration of IP global enables.

hpicfIpStaticRouteGroup.name: hpicfIpStaticRouteGroup
hpicfIpStaticRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring IP static routes.

hpicfIpStaticNeighborGroup.name: hpicfIpStaticNeighborGroup
hpicfIpStaticNeighborGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring IP static neighbors.

hpicfIpCidrRouteGroup.name: hpicfIpCidrRouteGroup
hpicfIpCidrRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects for retrieving extended information about routes in the routing table.

hpicfInetCidrRouteGroup.name: hpicfInetCidrRouteGroup
hpicfInetCidrRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects for retrieving extended information about routes in the routing table.

hpicfArpBaseGroup.name: hpicfArpBaseGroup
hpicfArpBaseGroup.description: Basic ARP (address resolution protocol) configuration objects.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixGroup.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixGroup
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvPrefixGroup.description: The group of objects in a table for configuring the Router Advertisement options.

hpicfIpv6RtrAdvGroup.name: hpicfIpv6RtrAdvGroup
hpicfIpv6RtrAdvGroup.description: The group of objects in a table for configuring the Router Advertisement options.
